videos.headline: RS Hangargekar to Shankar, out Caught by Santner!! Big, big wicket!! What an IPL debut this young kid is having. This was an attempted yorker, falls marginally short and Shankar tries to dig it over the infield. Gets enough elevation but not the distance, and a back-tracking Santner always had eyes on the ball to complete a superb reverse cup. Shankar c Santner b RS Hangargekar 27(21) [4s-2 6s-1]

Tushar Deshpande to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Action replay delivery and this time Gill is gone. The GT opener goes for the big slap across the line again, but this time gets more elevation than distance. The elevation helps Gaikwad run in from the boundary ropes and complete a fine pouch. Shubman Gill c Gaikwad b Tushar Deshpande 63(36) [4s-6 6s-3]

Tushar Deshpande to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Action replay delivery and this time Gill is gone. The GT opener goes for the big slap across the line again, but this time gets more elevation than distance. The elevation helps Gaikwad run in from the boundary ropes and complete a fine pouch. Shubman Gill c Gaikwad b Tushar Deshpande 63(36) [4s-6 6s-3]

Jadeja to Hardik Pandya, out Bowled!! Knocked over!! This was a flat delivery on off that zipped through. Pandya goes for a cross batted sweep and the ball skids through before to take out his off stump. Didn't need to play a risky shot, ends up costing him the wicket today. Hardik Pandya b Jadeja 8(11)

RS Hangargekar to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Dhoni!! Gone!! Soft dismissal!! This was a length ball very wide, was the cutter. Sai Sudharsan went chasing to cut and gets a faint underedge that carries through to Dhoni. Sai Sudharsan has a wry smile on his face for playing at that, would have been wide otherwise...Is this CSK's route back in the game? Sai Sudharsan c Dhoni b RS Hangargekar 22(17) [4s-3]

RS Hangargekar to Saha, out Caught by Shivam Dube!! Hangargekar strikes in his first over. Saha flashes away from his body against this short ball and the top edge flies towards square third man. Dube sprints across to his right, keeps his eyes on the ball and completes a fantastic catch diving to his right. Saha is waiting on the sidelines to check out for the replays, but it's a clean catch. The opening partnership has been broken, so we can expect a few more wickets over the next few overs. Saha c Shivam Dube b RS Hangargekar 25(16) [4s-2 6s-2]

Shami to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Rashid Khan!! Shami's a strike bowler and he'll continue to be one. That's a comeback you can expect from him. Conceded a six against a short ball just on the last ball, and he challenges the batter with another short one. Shivam Dube goes for a pull just like he did on the last ball, but this time he ends up getting a top edge. Straight to Rashid at deep square leg and he's not going to miss out on those. Shivam Dube c Rashid Khan b Shami 19(18) [6s-1]

Alzarri Joseph to Jadeja, out Caught by Shankar!! Straight to Mr. 3D at deep mid-wicket. A full length delivery on middle and leg, and Jadeja flicks it stylishly. Gets enough elevation, but not the required distance. Wasn't that an easy catch, but Vijay Shankar stationed near the boundary makes it look like one. Reverse cups it and that's that for RJ for tonight. Jadeja c Shankar b Alzarri Joseph 1(2)

Alzarri Joseph to Gaikwad, out Caught by Shubman Gill!! So near, yet so far. That was a pretty high full toss, but just below the waist as confirmed by the third umpire. It was dipping in. Gaikwad was looking to whack that away to the fence, but couldn't middle it. Gill at long-on is quick to charge in as he completes a pretty impressive catch diving forward. End of a spectacular knock for Gaikwad. Some of those shots were simply outstanding. The change of bats results in his downfall. Gaikwad c Shubman Gill b Alzarri Joseph 92(50) [4s-4 6s-9]

Joshua Little to Rayudu, out Bowled!! Gives the charge to slog and is cleaned up! A slower off-cutter, Rayudu looks to swing down the ground but is beaten on the edge. It clatters into the stumps. Rayudu b Joshua Little 12(12) [6s-1]

Rashid Khan to Stokes, out Caught by Saha!! Definite edge there. Yes the finger goes up. Stokes is undone as he misjudges length, and goes back to a leg-break he should've been forward to. It's pushed through flat just outside off, Stokes tries punching it through cover but it skids through sharply, taking a nick to the keeper. Another good catch from Saha. Stokes c Saha b Rashid Khan 7(6) [4s-1]

Rashid Khan to Moeen Ali, out Caught by Saha!! Gone! Saha just about hangs onto it! Full outside off, Moeen swings hard looking to go over extra cover but edges it behind as Rashid strikes right back after the boundary. Moeen Ali c Saha b Rashid Khan 23(17) [4s-4 6s-1]

Shami to Conway, out Bowled!! 100 IPL wickets for Shami who has made a mess of the stumps! Full, fast, slanted in from round the wicket. And it's a very loose drive from Conway. His front foot doesn't go anywhere, the ball nips in sharply, goes through the gate and clatters into middle and off. Conway b Shami 1(6)
